<div id="review_1672237592" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1672237592" />
    <a title="Al George " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26693609-al-george"><img alt="Al George " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1456963253p2/26693609.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1672237592?book_show_action=true">Jun 18, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Al George " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Al George " href="/user/show/26693609-al-george">Al George </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1672237592" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10131798438566349465"><b>Bark at the moon</b><br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1467073980ra/19548951.gif' width='400' height='208' alt='howl' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> <br/><br/>Seriously, the entire time I listened to this book and read it (hello Whispersync), I kept hearing Ozzy belting out:<br/><blockquote>Those that the beast is looking for<br/>Listen in awe and you&apos;ll hear him<br/>Bark at the moon<br/>Hey yeah, bark at the moon</blockquote><br/><br/>Go figure. <br/><br/><b>Setting / Time / Genre:</b> Current. Mostly New York<br/><br/><b>Series:</b> Second in the series. <br/><br/><b>Sexy times:</b> Hot, hotty, hotterson. <br/> <br/><b>Plan on reading more by the author: </b> Uh huh. I&apos;m obsessed! <br/><br/><b>Synopsis:</b> So this is the story of Smitty, hot wolf man, and Jess, hot wil</span>
  <span id="freeText10131798438566349465" style="display:none"><b>Bark at the moon</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1467073980ra/19548951.gif" width="400" height="208" alt="howl" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br>Seriously, the entire time I listened to this book and read it (hello Whispersync), I kept hearing Ozzy belting out:<br><blockquote>Those that the beast is looking for<br>Listen in awe and you'll hear him<br>Bark at the moon<br>Hey yeah, bark at the moon</blockquote><br><br>Go figure. <br><br><b>Setting / Time / Genre:</b> Current. Mostly New York<br><br><b>Series:</b> Second in the series. <br><br><b>Sexy times:</b> Hot, hotty, hotterson. <br> <br><b>Plan on reading more by the author: </b> Uh huh. I'm obsessed! <br><br><b>Synopsis:</b> So this is the story of Smitty, hot wolf man, and Jess, hot wild dog. Ok, let's stop there and give a big ole howl to Shelley Laurentston. You embrace diversity and get back with your bad self. I love this woman for a not all white cast. Aaahoo!<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1467073980ra/19548952.gif" width="400" height="224" alt="howl2" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br>Now I have Werewolves of London in my head. Sheesh. Will my mental playlist ever end? Anyway...<br><br>Jess and Smitty have history. She's now all grown up and super successful and he's all so serious and becoming successful. This whole thing boils down to poor Smitty being afraid he's gonna go all cray and put the claim on Jess. Jess wants him to go all cray, down and dirty and claim her like the beast he is. Apparently, the two need some counseling because they don't tell each other this. <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1467073980ra/19548953.gif" width="245" height="170" alt="therapy" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br><b>Hero:</b> Smitty. Slow. Sexy. Southern. How's that for alliteration?<br><br><b>Heroine:</b> Jess. Overly cheerful with that damned dog disposition. She'd get on my last nerve, but there you go. That said, she's pretty funny. And she's damned tough. <br><br><b>Why it did or didn't work for me:</b> I adored it. We got to check in with the rest of the family and the other cast of characters and we met a few new ones. The wild dogs are not my favs, but who am I to be prejudice against them. It's not like they are real or anything. That said...there sure was some great attitude being thrown and a little shade here and there. It made me laugh out loud quite a few times and when I finish this series...I am totes gonna miss these guys. All of them. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10131798438566349465" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


